23 def hampel_filter_forloop(input_series, window_size, n_sigmas=3):
24  """
25  Implementation of Hampel Filter for outlier detection.
26 
27  Arguments
28  ----------
29  `input_series`: `np.array`
30  The input data to use for outlier detection.
31 
32  `window_size`: `int`
33  The sliding window size to use for the filter on
34  `input_series`.
35 
36  `n_sigmas`: `int`
37  The number of standard deviations to determine
38  what data points are outliers.
39  """
40  n = len(input_series)
41  new_series = input_series.copy()
42  k = 1.4826 # scale factor for Gaussian distribution
43  indices = []
44  # possibly use np.nanmedian
45  for i in range((window_size), (n - window_size)):
46  x0 = np.median(input_series[(i - window_size):(i + window_size)])
47  S0 = k * np.median(
48  np.abs(
49  input_series[
50  (i - window_size):(i + window_size)] - x0))
51  if (np.abs(input_series[i] - x0) > n_sigmas * S0):
52  new_series[i] = x0
53  indices.append(i)
54  return new_series, indices

57 class DynamicPoseData():

117  def clean_data(self, verbose=False):
118  """
119  Cleans the data.
120 
121  Arguments
122  ----------
123  `verbose`: `bool`
124  """
125  # Create nested dictionary to store data
126  data = copy.deepcopy(self.data)
127  for pose_name in self.pose_names:
128  for joint_name in self.joint_names:
129  for imu_name in self.imu_names:
130  d = self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][2:, :]
131  norms = np.linalg.norm(d[:, :3], axis=1)
132  norms, outliers_index = hampel_filter_forloop(norms, 10, 1)
133  idx = np.argmax(norms)
134 
135  # Save maximum angular velocity A of all time
136  w = d[:, 3]
137  w, outliers_index = hampel_filter_forloop(w, 10, 1)
138  max_w_idx = np.argmax(w)
139 
140  joint_accel = d[:, 4]
141  ja, outliers_index = \
142  hampel_filter_forloop(joint_accel, 10, 1)
143  # max_ja_idx = np.argmax(ja)
144  """
145  joints = d[:, 4:]
146  window = 50
147  rospy.loginfo(
148  utils.n2s(
149  self.data[pose_name]
150  [joint_name]
151  [imu_name][idx-window:idx+window+1, :7], 3))
152  if joint_name == self.joint_names[0]
153  and (imu_name in self.imu_names[:2]):
154  rospy.loginfo(
155  '[%s, %s, %s]'%(pose_name, joint_name, imu_name))
156  rospy.loginfo(utils.n2s(d[:window+1, :9], 3))
157  rospy.loginfo(
158  '[%ith Norm=%.3f (%.2f, %.2f, %.2f),
159  w=%.2f, joint accel=%.2f'%\
160  (idx, norms[idx], d[idx,0],
161  d[idx,1], d[idx,2], w[idx], ja[idx]))
162  rospy.loginfo(
163  '[%ith Norm=%.3f (%.2f, %.2f, %.2f),
164  w=%.2f, joint accel=%.2f'%\
165  (max_w_idx,
166  norms[max_w_idx], d[max_w_idx,0],
167  d[max_w_idx,1], d[max_w_idx,2],
168  w[max_w_idx], ja[max_w_idx]))
169  rospy.loginfo('[%ith Norm=%.3f (%.2f, %.2f, %.2f),
170  w=%.2f, joint accel=%.2f'%\
171  (max_ja_idx, norms[max_ja_idx],
172  d[max_ja_idx,0], d[max_ja_idx,1],
173  d[max_ja_idx,2], w[max_ja_idx], ja[max_ja_idx]))
174  """
175 
176  data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name] = \
177  self.data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][idx, :]
178  data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][3] = w[idx]
179  data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name][4] = w[max_w_idx]
180 
181  if verbose:
182  rospy.loginfo(data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name])
183  d = data[pose_name][joint_name][imu_name]
184  rospy.loginfo(
185  '[%s, %s, %s] (%.3f, %.3f, %.3f)'
186  % (pose_name, joint_name, imu_name,
187  d[0], d[1], d[2]))

233  self.imu_topics = ['imu_data0', 'imu_data1', 'imu_data2',
234  'imu_data3', 'imu_data4', 'imu_data5', 'imu_data6']
235 
236  self.ready = False
237  self.curr_positions = [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0]
238  self.curr_pose_name = self.pose_names[0]
239  self.curr_joint_name = self.joint_names[0]
240  self.max_angular_velocity = -np.inf
241  self.prev_w = 0.0
242  self.prev_t = 0.000001

244 
245  rospy.loginfo(self.joint_names)
246 
247  # data storage
248  self.data_storage = \

252  # Subscribe to IMUs

256  def callback(self, data):
257  """
258  A callback function for IMU topics
259 
260  Arguments
261  ----------
262  data: sensor_msgs.msg.Imu
263  IMU data. Please refer to the official documentation.
264  http://docs.ros.org/melodic/api/sensor_msgs/html/msg/Imu.html
265  """
266  if self.ready:
267  accel = data.linear_acceleration
268  joint_angles = [
269  self.controller.joint_angle(name) for name in self.joint_names]
270 
271  if self.curr_joint_name == self.joint_names[0] and \
272  data.header.frame_id == 'imu_link0':
273  pass
274  # rospy.loginfo(utils.n2s(
275  # np.array([accel.x, accel.y, accel.z])))
276 
277  curr_t = rospy.get_rostime().to_sec()
278  dt = curr_t - self.prev_t
279 
280  curr_w = self.controller.joint_velocity(self.curr_joint_name)
281  curr_A = abs(curr_w)
282 
283  try:
284  self.curr_acc = (curr_w - self.prev_w) / dt
285  except Exception:
286  pass
287 
288  if curr_A > self.max_angular_velocity:
289  self.max_angular_velocity = curr_A
290  # rospy.loginfo
291  # (self.curr_joint_name + ' ' +
292  # data.header.frame_id + ' ' +
293  # 'Max Angular Velocity: %.4f'%(curr_A))
294 
295  self.data_storage.append(
296  self.curr_pose_name, # for each defined initial pose
297  self.curr_joint_name, # for each excited joint
298  data.header.frame_id, # for each imu
299  np.array([
300  accel.x, accel.y, accel.z,
301  self.max_angular_velocity, self.curr_acc] + joint_angles))
302 
303  self.prev_w = curr_w
304  self.prev_t = curr_t

306  def move_like_sine_dynamic(self):
307  """
308  This will move the joint of the robot arm like a sine wave
309  for all joints for all defined poses.
310  """
311  self.controller.set_joint_position_speed(speed=1.0)
312 
313  freq = rospy.get_param('/oscillation_frequency')
314  A = rospy.get_param('/oscillation_magnitude')
315 
316  for pose in self.poses_list:
317  positions, \
318  _, pose_name = pose[0], pose[1], pose[2] # noqa: F841
319  self.curr_positions = positions
320  self.curr_pose_name = pose_name
321  self.controller.publish_positions(positions, sleep=1)
322  print('At Position: ' + pose_name,
323  map(int, RAD2DEG*np.array(positions)))
324 
325  for i, joint_name in enumerate(self.joint_names):
326  self.curr_joint_name = joint_name
327  self.max_angular_velocity = -np.inf
328  self.prev_w = \
329  self.controller.joint_velocity(self.curr_joint_name)
330  self.prev_t = rospy.get_rostime().to_sec()
331 
332  # Prepare for publishing a trajectory
333  velocities = np.zeros(len(self.joint_names))
334  accelerations = np.zeros(len(self.joint_names))
335  poss = copy.deepcopy(positions)
336 
337  # stopping time
338  self.ready = True
339  now = rospy.get_rostime()
340  while True:
341  t = (rospy.get_rostime() - now).to_sec()
342 
343  # Oscillated Pos, Vel, Acc
344  position = A/(2*pi*freq)*(1-math.cos(2 * pi * freq * t))
345  velocity = A*math.sin(2 * pi * freq * t)
346  acceleration = 2*pi*freq*A*math.cos(2 * pi * freq * t)
347 
348  poss[i] = positions[i] + position
349  velocities[i] = velocity
350  accelerations[i] = acceleration
351 
352  self.controller.publish_trajectory(
353  poss, velocities, accelerations, None)
354 
355  if t > OSCILLATION_TIME:
356  break
357 
358  self.ready = False
359  rospy.sleep(1)
